{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 13,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 13 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:1",
      "text": "A wise son is obedient to his father: but a disobedient son will be destroyed.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:2",
      "text": "A good man shall eat of the fruits of righteousness: but the lives of transgressors shall perish before their time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:3",
      "text": "He that keeps his own mouth keeps his own life: but he that is hasty with his lips shall bring terror upon himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:4",
      "text": "Every slothful man desires, but the hands of the active are diligent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:5",
      "text": "A righteous man hates an unjust word: but an ungodly man is ashamed, and will have no confidence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:7",
      "text": "There are some who, having nothing, enrich themselves: and there are some who bring themselves down in the midst of much wealth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:8",
      "text": "A man’s own wealth is the ransom of his life: but the poor endures not threatening.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:9",
      "text": "The righteous always have light: but the light of the ungodly is quenched. Crafty souls go astray in sins: but just men pity, and are merciful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:10",
      "text": "A bad man does evil with insolence: but they that are judges of themselves are wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:11",
      "text": "Wealth gotten hastily with iniquity is diminished: but he that gathers for himself with godliness shall be increased. The righteous is merciful, and lends.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:12",
      "text": "Better is he that begins to help heartily, than he that promises and leads another to hope: for a good desire is a tree of life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:13",
      "text": "He that slights a matter shall be slighted of it: but he that fears the commandment has health of soul. To a crafty son there shall be nothing good: but a wise servant shall have prosperous doings, and his way shall be directed aright.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:14",
      "text": "The law of the wise is fountain of life: but the man void of understanding shall die by a snare.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:15",
      "text": "Sound discretion gives favour, and to know the law is the part of a sound understanding: but the ways of scorners tend to destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:16",
      "text": "Every prudent man acts with knowledge: but the fool displays his own mischief.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:17",
      "text": "A rash king shall fall into mischief: but a wise messenger shall deliver him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:18",
      "text": "Instruction removes poverty and disgrace: but he that attends to reproofs shall be honoured.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:19",
      "text": "The desires of the godly gladden the soul, but the works of the ungodly are far from knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:20",
      "text": "If thou walkest with wise men thou shalt be wise: but he that walks with fools shall be known.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:21",
      "text": "Evil shall pursue sinners; but good shall overtake the righteous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:22",
      "text": "A good man shall inherit children’s children; and the wealth of ungodly men is laid up for the just.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:23",
      "text": "The righteous shall spend many years in wealth: but the unrighteous shall perish suddenly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:24",
      "text": "He that spares the rod hates his son: but he that loves, carefully chastens him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.13.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 13:25",
      "text": "A just man eats and satisfies his soul: but the souls of the ungodly are in want.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
